        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In contrast to ZF1, ZF2 unnecessarily encodes headers even if they contain only ASCII characters. Demo:\r\n\r\n$mail = new Zend\\Mail\\Message();\r\n$mail->setEncoding('UTF-8');\r\n$mail->setFrom('example@example.org', 'My Name');\r\necho $mail->toString();\r\n\r\nResult:\r\n\r\nFrom: =?UTF-8?Q?My=20Name?= <example@example.org>\r\n\r\nExpected result:\r\n\r\nFrom: My Name <example@example.org>"
        },
