            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51141",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steffen",
                        "name": "steffen",
                        "displayName": "Steffen Weber",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think the method Zend\\Mime\\Mime::isPrintable can be used to determine if a header has to be encoded.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steffen",
                        "name": "steffen",
                        "displayName": "Steffen Weber",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-17T12:19:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-17T12:19:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51145",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As workaround you can do one of the following options:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$mail->headers()->get('From')->setEncoding('ASCII');\r\n\r\n$mail->headers()->setEncoding('ASCII');\r\n\r\n$mail->getHeader('From', null)->setEncoding('ASCII');\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-18T14:38:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-18T14:38:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51283",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steffen",
                        "name": "steffen",
                        "displayName": "Steffen Weber",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've just downloaded ZF2 Beta 5. Even the \"Date\" header is encoded. Maybe some classes like Zend\\Mail\\Header\\Date should just ignore calls of their \"setEncoding\" method?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steffen",
                        "name": "steffen",
                        "displayName": "Steffen Weber",
                        "active": true
                    },
